# Standardized OMOP Data ReadMe

The Answer ALS clinical data were standardized to the Observational Medical Outcomes Partnership (OMOP) Common Data Model (CDM) version 5.4 to enable integration with other OMOP-based datasets, such as those maintained by ALS TDI, C-Path, and others. 

Researchers interested in combined analyses with other datasets like ALS TDI may find it advantageous to use the standardized OMOP versions.

The extract transform load (ETL) process was designed to balance several objectives: preserving the original meaning of the source data, ensuring interoperability with other datasets within Neuromine and external OMOP datasets, and maintaining utility for downstream analyses (including use with OHDSI tools). The standardization adhered to best practices established by the Observational Health Data Sciences and Informatics (OHDSI) community, including official documentation, workgroup guidance, and community forums.

# Understanding OMOP

## OMOP CDM Version

This dataset uses OMOP CDM version 5.4

[CDMv5.4 Diagram](https://ohdsi.github.io/CommonDataModel/index.html):  
![Diagram][https://ohdsi.github.io/CommonDataModel/index.html]

[CDMv5.4 Specifications](https://ohdsi.github.io/CommonDataModel/cdm54.html): Breakdown of all CDMv5.4 OMOP tables and variables and their definitions.

## Resources

[OMOP CDM Background](https://ohdsi.github.io/CommonDataModel/background.html): History and design principles of OMOP.

[OHDSI Website](https://ohdsi.org): (Observational Health Data Sciences and Informatics) Website for the community that developed the OMOP common data model and associated standard tools and continues to support them.

[OHDSI Forums](https://forums.ohdsi.org): OHDSI community publicly discusses issues and activities related to implementation, development, research, etc. around the OMOP CDM.

[Book of OHDSI](https://ohdsi.github.io/TheBookOfOhdsi/): The Book of OHDSI provides a guide to standardizing and analyzing healthcare data for observational research.

[OHDSI GitHub](https://github.com/OHDSI): Knowledgebase and tools for working with OMOP data.

[OHDSI YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@OHDSI): Presentations and educational materials surrounding OHDSI and OMOP.

[OHDSI Wiki](https://www.ohdsi.org/web/wiki/doku.php): Documentation and resources.

# Mapping

## Table Assignment Summary

| OMOP Table | Source Tables Pulled From |
| :---- | :---- |
| person.csv | Demographics.csv |
| death.csv | Mortality.csv |
| condition\_occurrence.csv | AALSHXFX.csv, Medical\_History.csv, NEUROLOG.csv |
| observation.csv | AALSDXFX.csv, AALSHXFX.csv, ALSFRS\_R.csv, Environmental\_Questionnaire.csv, Family\_History\_Log.csv |
| measurement.csv | ALS\_Gene\_Mutations.csv, Auxiliary\_Chemistry\_Labs.csv, Vital\_Signs.csv |
| drug\_exposure.csv | ANSWER\_ALS\_Medications\_Log.csv, Medical\_History.csv |
| device\_exposure.csv | Medical\_History.csv |
| procedure\_occurrence.csv | Medical\_History.csv |
